An Act establishing distinctive license plates.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 2 of chapter 90 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after the
2 tenth paragraph, as appearing in the 2020 Official Edition, the following paragraph:-
3 The registrar shall furnish, at the request of an owner of a motorcycle or a motor vehicle,
4 a license plate that bears the motto “In God We Trust.” The registrar may charge a fee directly
5 attributable to the cost of issuance of such a design upon the initial issuance of such specialized
6 license plates. This motto shall be made available to augment all standard and specialized license
7 plate designs issued within the Commonwealth. There shall additionally be an annual $20 fee for
8 such “In God We Trust” plates in addition to the established registration fee for private
9 passenger motor vehicles and motorcycles. For the purpose of this paragraph, the word
10 “motorcycles” shall not include motorized bicycles.
